name: Afterburn
description: Afterburn's large size combined with its imperviousness to heat has made it perfect for rescuing people and Miscrits from fires

name: Fairyblossom
description: Fairyblossom is a favorite of teen girls all over Miscria, many of which choose to decorate their bedrooms with paintings and stuffed toys of the creature

name: Clawmurai
description: A strategy expert, Clawmurai has an incredible grasp of the art of war and is an asset to any Miscrit team

name: Serpasoar
description: Serpasoar's head prefers to engage its opponents straight-on as a warrior, whereas its tail fights dirty and will perform surprise attacks whenever the opportunity presents itself

name: Bloomane
description: A kind and gentle leader, Bloomane is helpful to any team because of its calming influence on wilder Miscrits

name: Wiquill
description: The blue flames on Wiquill's back and face are widely thought to be made of the hottest substance in all of Miscria

name: Squalrus
description: The ever-moving shield of water around Squalrus can keep it warm in even the most frigid of Miscrian climates

name: Coraswine
description: Legends say Coraswine has rescued many lost sailors by letting them fall asleep on its back at sea and floating them to safety

name: Subterhuge
description: Subterhuge's strength, speed, and superior sense of smell make it indispensable for search and rescue operations

name: Infernus
description: Many wealthy families try to keep the beautiful Infernus as nothing more than a pet. A true warrior at heart, Infernus is unhappy unless permitted to battle

name: Anublaze
description: It is extremely rare to encounter an Anublaze that can be described as anything but wickedly self-serving, but they do exist

name: Snapdragon
description: Snapdragon looks fairly innocuous until it opens its large, pincer-like mouth, which is when people generally commence running away

name: Grastodon
description: Grastodon's giant stump legs can sometimes begin to grow into the ground if it sleeps for long periods of time

name: Aquine
description: Few people see the shy Aquine, and most who do mistake it for anything from a shark to a beautiful mermaid

name: Kang Fu
description: Full of confidence and inner calm, Kang Fu feels it can win any fight it enters, and often tries to talk other Miscrits out of their challenge

name: Willoak
description: An ancient protector of the forest, Willoak is thought to be made from part of the Elder Tree itself

name: Kalamos
description: The exact number of tentacles that any given Kalamos has is a difficult figure to ascertain, leading some to believe the number changes daily

name: Krakenhook
description: Krakenhook can sometimes be spotted trying to command legions of water-type Miscrits far out at sea

name: Aukamotive
description: Miscrian engineers have been trying to find a way to utilize Aukamotive's unique powers to create new forms of transportation

name: Mallardon
description: Mallardon is sweet-natured and loves petting soft things, but its inability to judge its own strength sometimes gets it into trouble

name: Monfiki
description: Monfiki is constantly chattering as though it expects everyone around it to actually understand what it's talking about, but to everyone but its own kind, the sounds are unintelligible

name: Ongabonga
description: Experienced Miscrian Adventurers know that when lost in the forest at night, Ongabonga's glowing arm is an excellent guide

name: Dark Afterburn
description: A scorched path of destruction is left in the wake of Dark Afterburn. It'll walk slowly ahead of it in hopes that mankind tries to catch it... and fail

name: Dark Fairyblossom
description: Dark Fairyblossom's personality is best understood by watching it viciously and purposefully try to rid the land of all regular Fairyblossoms

name: Dark Clawmurai
description: The Dark Clawmurai has evolved not just through time, but through pain. Its journey combined with its age creates a Miscrit that can pick its battles... and win them all

name: Eruptacus
description: Equipped with as much power as a small volcano, Eruptacus has been known to take down dozens of smaller foes single-handedly

name: Abomino
description: Even on the hottest days of a Miscrian summer, Abomino is covered in ice, and uses its frozen coat to help cool down Miscrits who've been overcome by exhaustion

name: Minotorch
description: The rare and beautiful Minotorch is a topic of many ancient Miscrian tales of myth and legend

name: Panthundra
description: A single Panthundra has enough electricity coursing through its body to power an entire village with ease

name: Sagittarion
description: Sagittarion has a deep sense of ritual and tradition, and it's generally best to avoid encounters with it. Even the simplest exchange may be considered an insult

name: Demolasher
description: Demolasher has been known to accidentally destroy everything from trees to fully complete buildings when it gets too excited

name: Edison Ray
description: The high levels of electrical currents coming from Edison Ray can sometimes cause the very surface of the water to crackle as it moves

name: Glidengale
description: When Glidengale is in the air, its large tail merges with its wings in order to allow it to fly faster and farther than it could with only feathers

name: Sphynxus
description: Sphynxus spends much of its time thinking up riddles to tell other Miscrits. It prefers mind games to battling, although it's still a great fighter

name: Wyndasia
description: Many stories say that the gem on Wyndasia's head changes colors with its mood, but as it's very seldom anything but serene, this hasn't been proven

name: Medustung
description: When Medustung holds its four lightning balls above its head and merges them into one, it produces an incredible amount of energy

name: Geotoad
description: Geotoad can't fully close its mouth without chipping at least one of its teeth, which leads to it constantly eating things that fly into its mouth while it's moving

name: Buzzcargo
description: Despite Buzzcargo's off-putting and slightly gross appearance, it is a highly powerful Miscrit with a sweet disposition

name: Mineram
description: There isn't a single material occurring in nature that can't be smashed by a charge from Mineram and its incredible horns

name: Hootray
description: Hootray can always be spotted flying upwards with the rising sun, leading to many myths being told about it actually being part of the sun

name: Antennious
description: Antennious primarily moves around at night. It darkens its orbs while it follows its prey, then brightly lights itself in order to temporarily blind its foe

name: Zephyrgeist
description: There is no spookier sight when entering a battle than seeing a large crowd of Zephyrgeists from afar, with only their armor visible

name: Primordius
description: Primordius's shield is made from the fossil of the first Miscrit that it defeated in battle, back in prehistoric times

name: Rocklodon
description: Rocklodon possesses more strength in its large, formidable tail than many Miscrits do in their entire body

name: Clobberilla
description: The massive energy balls wielded by Clobberilla possess enough power to light up an entire countryside

name: Hanuphoon
description: Hanuphoon is rarely, if ever, seen actually landing on the ground. Through a combination of powerful wings and zen meditation, it floats constantly

name: Zapire
description: Although Zapire is strong, it never attacks with anything other than the lightning charges that it hides behind its wings

name: Stalagfright
description: Stalagfright's spikes have massive barbs that are incredibly difficult to remove. They are its primary weapon, and if one of them breaks off, it regenerates another within a day

name: Scorpionyx
description: Scorpionyx loves nothing more than hiding deep within caves, where it is nearly indistinguishable from its surroundings, then opening its deep red eyes in order to frighten whomever's hunting it

name: Glitterglint
description: Glitterglint is said to be the most joyous of all Miscrits, and the size of the glow and sparkles it emits is strongly affected by its happiness

name: Thornaxis
description: Thornaxis can turn barren land into a dense, lush forest in no time at all with the seedlings that grow from its limbs

name: Warro
description: Warro are considered by many to be one of the most intelligent Miscrits. Warro have much longer life spans than most Miscrits and as such are very wise

name: Nessilisk
description: Nessilisk perceives almost every look or glance in its general direction as an insult, and it's usually safer to just stare pointedly at the ground while in its presence

name: Cheetorch
description: Cheetorch can sometimes be found in the top of lighthouses. Its tail produces an incredible amount of light, and its large ears help it hear so well that it can detect lost ships from far away

name: Dynamellow
description: The static charges within Dynamellow's horns help to provide even more power to its lumbering headbutt attacks it is fond of performing

name: Tuzee
description: Although Tuzee can fly, each of its wings often have a different idea of what direction and speed they want to go. It usually only flies short distances before growing tired of the effort

name: Quarriock
description: The rocks lining Quarriock's back flatten when it is relaxed, but because Quarriock virtually never calms down enough for that to happen, few have seen it

name: Excavior
description: Excavior is a highly sought-after treasure hunter. Its sense of smell is unparalleled, and once it decides what it is after, it will do whatever it takes to uncover what it wants

name: Triceratron
description: Triceratron's horns are mainly useful for intimidation, because they are actually far more delicate than they initially appear. They do, however, grow back if broken

name: Ostral
description: Despite the heavy metal plating that covers nearly its entire body, Ostral is incredibly fast. It can summon breezes to help it forward, which helps it reach blinding speeds

name: Hydroslam
description: Hydroslam often just floats in the shallows of Sunfall Shores, where it is extremely difficult to distinguish from just a floating mass of seaweed until it opens its large, purple eyes

name: Gazaereal
description: Although Gazareal can easily fly, it relies more often on its incredibly powerful hind legs to move it around. It easily accommodates riders in between its second set of wings for both ground and air travel

name: Leviafin
description: Leviafin uses its tail for many things, including combat, picking things up, and investigating its surroundings. The end of the tail is much more sensitive than its fins

name: Derelicro
description: Derelicro's remarkable stench can almost act as an attack in and of itself. It can sometimes cause an opponents eyes to water from its strength

name: Preliator
description: Preliator, always trying to redeem itself for the selfish ways of the past, can always be counted on to help innocents in need

name: Zzzap
description: When Zzzap really wants to knock an enemy out, it channels the lightning power in the rest of its body completely into its stinger

name: Minninnewah
description: When Minninnewah has taken someone under its protection, it will stop at nothing to ensure that no harm comes to them

name: Dustelle
description: Dustelle is very shy, and when it feels someone watching, it whips the ground around it into a frenzy and disappears into the dust cloud

name: Reaping Gourd
description: Seeing a Reaping Gourd is incredibly rare, and is universally held to be a harbinger of bad luck. Many adventurers fear having one in their party, while others use the fear of others to their advantage

name: Clawsickle
description: Clawsickle rewards nice Miscrits with mercy, and punishes naughty Miscrits with the crushing blow of defeat

name: Tuskalate
description: Tuskalate is a proud, fearless warrior. No one can be sure where exactly it came from, but its convictions about right and wrong are unwavering

name: Dark Edison Ray
description: The only warning you'll receive about Dark Edison Ray's approach is the faint crackling under the water. If you're lucky, you'll have enough time to get away

name: Dark Geotoad
description: Dark Geotoad takes great pleasure in punishing any Miscrits that are foolish enough to get close to its horribly sharp crystal teeth

name: Rebound
description: Rebound has recovered from its previous heartbreak to be even stronger and more powerful than ever before, not to mention happier

name: Dark Bloomane
description: After being rejected time and time again by adventurers, Dark Bloomane turned into something terrible. It swore it would never again be considered weak

name: Dark Cheetorch
description: Dark Cheetorch has been known to attack the Cheetorches that guard lighthouses. It then draws ships onto the rocks to be destroyed

name: Dark Coraswine
description: Dark Coraswine tricks lost sailors into climbing onto its back, only to drift them further out to sea for its own amusement

name: Violimp
description: When Violimp pounds its hands on the ground, the booming sound that results is terribly loud and intimidating to its foes

name: Dark Hootray
description: Dark Hootray's talons are colored a dark crimson because they're covered in many, many layers of dried blood

name: Dark Warro
description: Dark Warro is extremely intelligent, and it uses its intelligence to take advantage of every opportunity for cruelty

name: Dark Dynamellow
description: When one looks into Dark Dynamellow's eyes, there is a fleeting sense of what a kind, gentle, and happy creature it could have been

name: Dark Squalrus
description: Dark Squalrus can conjure up a massive forcefield of water whenever it sees someone approaching that it doesn't like... which is everyone

name: Cheepers
description: Cheepers can only fly a few inches off the ground due to its weight. It seems to believe it's soaring high through the air, though

name: Dark Rocklodon
description: Dark Rocklodon's preferred battle tactic is to latch onto its opponent with its terrible jaws and then beat it senseless with its tail. It is shockingly brutal

name: Dark Infernus
description: Because Dark Infernus is beautiful, many have tried to tame it. No one has ever survived the attempt

name: Dark Grastodon
description: Dark Grastodon's legs sometimes grow straight into the ground. This causes areas of dead grass anywhere that it happens

name: Genesis
description: Genesis and her progeny are absolutely fearless and will protect each other at any cost. They never leave each other's sides

name: Dark Aquine
description: Dark Aquine draws in onlookers by pretending to be a mermaid, and then it brings them to a watery grave

name: Dark Kang Fu
description: Dark Kang Fu is constantly filled with rage. Some believe the red markings on its body are actually tattoos made with the blood of its enemies

name: Dark Glidengale
description: Dark Glidengale seems to travel at the speed of darkness, as it fills the sky with its deep black wings and smokey tail, dashing around within the shadows it creates

name: Zeusicus
description: Zeusicus is often very busy with battling all day, but he makes sure to spend quality time with his family once the day is done

name: Vesuvion
description: When Vesuvion is angry, its whole body erupts in bright green flames. This is exhausting for Vesuvion, so it tries to remain calm and level-headed as much as possible

name: Incineron
description: Incineron's long, flaming tongue can light fires with incredible precision. Its fires burn without producing smoke, which is part of why Incineron itself is so sought after

name: Gigantula
description: Although Gigantula moves very slowly, it is able to get several attacks in at once by using its many arms and claws

name: Praze
description: The claws on Praze's feet leave tiny scorch marks on the ground wherever it goes. For this reason, it's very easy to track

name: Popiller
description: Popiller got its name from the way it rolls around like a ball, and then pops its head out excitedly when it reaches its destination

name: Aviona
description: Aviona collects beautiful blooms while it flies, and adds them to its collection that it keeps with it at all times

name: Obsidiape
description: The heat emanating from Obsidiape's hands is equal to the steam from inside an erupting volcano, and is highly dangerous

name: Miraca
description: The variety of fruits that grow from Miraca's tail are believed to be the juiciest and most delicious fruit in all of Miscria

name: Pixiuma
description: Pixiuma almost never attacks first. It prefers to be slow and deliberate with its initial moves, then unleashing a powerful onslaught once its foe's guard is down

name: Growliath
description: Growliath is fiercely unpredictable, and sometimes difficult to control. Its mood swings are unparalleled, and no two Growliaths are entirely alike

name: Osteowraith
description: Osteowraith has been around for as long as anyone can remember, and much longer. Many believe it helped to create the land of Aerobia, and has been there ever since

name: Ripcurlio
description: Although Ripcurlio could simply walk around normally if it wanted, it chooses instead to float around on a sort of pillow made of water

name: Convincer
description: Convincer is often called upon to help with demolition operations. It can make quick work of any structure with its destructive tail

name: Tesladon
description: Tesladon can be incredibly precise with its lightning strikes. No matter how far up in the air it is, it can choose one precise spot to hit

name: Majestrike
description: Majestrike takes itself very seriously. It treats every battle as a performance, and always attacks with the utmost grace

name: Alionyx
description: Alionyx has a very stubborn personality. When it doesn't want to do something, it throws a silent tantrum by driving its gem claws into the ground so it's unmovable

name: Bifurcrystal
description: Bifurcrystal's entire body can be used as a weapon. Its tails are sharp, its tongue acts as a whip, and its teeth can crush anything

name: Hawkogan
description: Hawkogan carries two swords. It waits for an opponent fierce and noble enough to deserve to be gifted one of the weapons

name: Napoleon
description: Napoleon is extremely possessive of its territory. It doesn't like to share, although it does tolerate a few select other Miscrits

name: Kinginrin
description: Kinginrin slithers on its belly, but can also create winds powerful enough that it appears to be walking on four legs

name: Chiroptera
description: Chiroptera can send out supersonic lightning bolts in order to find food. They're undetectable to other creatures

name: Valrog
description: Valrog can only be found near a highly active volcano. It simply appears, leading many to believe it's made of a substance from inside the Volcano

name: Coyver
description: Coyver has a very one-track mind. Once it has set its sights on something that it wants, it will not stop to sleep or eat until its goal is met

name: Sulfurious
description: The odor that emanates from Sulfurious is so putrid, so off-putting, and so rotten that hardly anyone with an intact sense of smell can stand to go near

name: Napalm
description: Napalm flings fireballs from its hands at such a remarkably rapid rate that they are almost impossible to avoid

name: Primordion
description: Because Primordion is so loud, it never has the element of surprise on its side. Luckily, it's so strong that this doesn't hurt its chances too much

name: Dischord
description: Dischord can control the amount of wind in each of its armor pipes with perfect precision, to create beautiful music, or head-pounding noise

name: Stabbles
description: When Stabbles gets really heated during a battle, the flames from its body turn a bright blue due to their temperature

name: Dozer
description: Dozer's sheer physical strength is unparalleled. Lifting up an entire house is no more difficult for it than lifting a feather

name: Magmutt
description: Magmutt has been called the most loyal of all Miscrits, and it will never leave its adventurer's side once they've bonded

name: Stomprage
description: Stomprage is an excellent battler, but also greatly enjoys being of service to adventurers by efficiently delivering messages over great distance

name: Tornadouse
description: Even though Tornadouse has watery wings, it doesn't use them to fly. If it wants to soar into the air, it uses the small cyclone at its feet

name: Fangale
description: Fangale's four eyes enable it to make incredible maneuvers while it flies through the air. It never loses sight of anything

name: Verdauntless
description: Verdauntless takes great pride in keeping all of its gems spotlessly polished and gleaming, even right after a battle

name: Patriot
description: The incandescence of Patriot's independence glows brightly throughout the night, never fading, always continuing on

name: Ferocilux
description: Ferocilux isn't really as ferocious as it appears. That snarling, angry grimace is just how its face looks naturally

name: Tikki
description: Tikki's fork-like tail is quite deadly. Not only can it pierce through solid armor, but it also delivers several thousand joules of electrical energy into anything it strikes

name: Flamydosaurus
description: Flamydosaurus smells terrible, like sulfur mixed with burning hair, but its personality is so vibrant that most people don't mind the stench

name: Ninjat
description: Ninjat moves so quickly that it doesnt need to make itself invisible to avoid beeing seen. It simply zooms around as quickly as it needs to

name: Frankensnarl
description: Frankensnarl's exposed brain may look vulnerable, but it is protected by a current that could shock anyone into a coma

name: Foil Mallardon
description: People can't help but hug a Foil Mallardon. It sometimes sends people to the hospital though when it hugs back

name: Foil Primordius
description: Foil Primordius's stony lance makes a beautiful, albeit deadly, sight during its fierce battles with other Miscrits

name: Foil Clobberilla
description: The massive energy balls wielded by Foil Clobberilla are so shiny, they actually light up an entire countryside

name: Shackle
description: Shackle, despite its name, is not currently nor has it ever been used to hold Miscrian prisoners at bay

name: Foil Edison Ray
description: Foil Edison Ray is highly electric, but it prefers to use physical attacks. It saves its lightning energy for performances

name: Nova
description: Nova's favorite activities are battling, spending time with friends, and eating absolutely everything in sight

name: Poggle
description: Poggle's little feet are incredibly strong, managing to hold up its absurdly heavy body without fail. It helps that Poggle enjoys laying on its side

name: Foil Napalm
description: Foil Napalm's fireballs are easy to spot. They burn so fiercely that even the surrounding air is hot enough to cause third degree burns

name: Light Valrog
description: Light Valrog cannot be found under normal circumstances, and no one is quite sure where it comes from

name: Lapinfire
description: Lapinfire is generally too dignified to perform tricks, but for special occasions it sometimes shows off its moves

name: Rolox
description: Rolox's ax delivers justice, truth and knowledge to people all over Miscria. The small egg contained within it is said to hold an incredible secret

name: Airyn
description: Airyn's spooky and otherworldly appearance during flight can be quite frightening in the night skies over Miscria

name: Charrill
description: Charrill doesn't naturally have flame markers on its exoskeleton. They are used as decoration to set it apart

name: Gargantubolt
description: Gargantubolt is entirely at peace with its odd looks and large stature, and doesn't let anyone make it feel left out

name: Mongrian
description: Mongrian's center head is always stoic, and constantly vigilant. The other two heads are a bit more unpredictable

name: Rivett
description: Rivett doesn't seem to be able to communicate. Instead it just makes a low whirring sound constantly as it moves

name: Kvetch
description: Kvetch simply won't tolerate rudeness, and uses its strength to enforce its strict policy of politeness

name: Weylani
description: Weylani's otherworldly appearance is part of why it has the reputation of being unapproachable and uninterested

name: Chubbles
description: Chubbles stomps around in its watery body in a generally terrible temper, spraying little droplets with every step

name: Shamar
description: Shamar is held in very high esteem by Miscrians, and many legends surround its history and origins

name: Bolderon
description: Bolderon is a fierce leader with exceptional magic birthed in earth and nature. One with the land it lives upon, Bolderon is a favorite among adventurers

name: Doruden
description: Like heaven itself, Doruden shines at the sky. As long as its candles burn, the land will live in peace and natural harmony

name: Wachter
description: Wachter is an absolute earthen beast. With precision it destroys its foes, and has the speed to prevent them from escaping

name: Blowhemoth
description: Blowhemoth is a wonderful addition to any Miscrit team. Fast, predatory and determined, Blowhemoth is one of the best Miscrits in Miscria

name: Arcanaclaw
description: Arcanaclaw has powerful claw'd tendrils and a reddened hood, and is one of the fiercest water Miscrits available. They are especially quiet in the water

name: Spoiler
description: Spoiler is a hodge-podge of skill and fury. Its body is revolting against itself

name: Blighted Bloomane
description: After being infected and covered in plague, Blighted Bloomane has devolved into hunting and destroying anything it can find

name: Blighted Afterburn
description: Blighted Afterburn is one of the most feared Miscrits ever seen, as it's huge size and weight clear most anything out of its way

name: Vampsower
description: Vampsower believes they are the life of each and every party. Regardless of what anyone says

name: Light Coyver
description: Light Coyver is terrifying in battle, often surprising its adversaries with incredible magical attacks followed by overwhelming power in its bite

name: Light Abomino
description: Light Abomino is intensely reclusive and almost never spotted in the wild. Some say it is because, should it see you, you may never see another thing again

name: Light Convincer
description: Light Convincer is named after its ability to 'convince' any opponent that it might be wise to avoid it in battle at all cost

name: Light Tesladon
description: Light Tesladon is a foremost master of Nature and Lightning. It can strike with both with little notice and extreme precision. Even Tesladon is cautious around it

name: Light Subterhuge
description: Light Subterhuge has mastered the Physical-Elemental combo abilities with such grace that only those unaware of its abilities dare face it

name: Light Panthundra
description: The ominous presence of Light Panthundra can be enough to defeat opponents. When you add its devastating attacks, it's a truly terrifying force

name: Dark Gigantula
description: Although Dark Gigantula moves very slowly, it is deceptively dexterous and able to strike with deadly accuracy in multiple directions simultaneously

name: Light Willoak
description: Light Willoak was once seen carrying several Willoaks away from an angry mob of Elite Willoaks. There is considerable strife among the various breeds

name: Krakyn
description: Krakyn is an apex predator of the deep. Even the most powerful sharks and water Miscrits flee in terror when it approaches

name: Blighted Airyn
description: Blighted Airyn drifts through the night like a ghostly specter, its decayed feathers scattering an eerie, glowing dust that lingers long after it vanishes

name: Blighted Edison Ray
description: Blighted Edison Ray is highly electric, but prefers to use blighted physical attacks. It saves its lightning energy for the most unfortunate foes it meets

name: Dark Kalamos
description: Dark Kalamos has a fixed, unchanging number of tentacles. However, no one can seem to agree on what that number actually is

name: Gorgonthunder
description: Gorgonthunder's might earned it the reverence of the moon's ancient inhabitants. It was so highly regarded that it was chosen as a guardian of sacred relics and temples

name: Dark Anublaze
description: Dark Anublaze is an unrelenting predator. Its blazing speed and scorching flames leave no room for doubtthis creature is power incarnate, with nothing holding it back

name: Dark Aukamotive
description: Dark Aukamotive moves with terrifying force, leaving plumes of black smoke in its wake. Some believe it's powered by an unnatural, never-ending inferno deep within

name: Dark Zephyrgeist
description: Dark Zephyrgeist wanders the land in silent authority, putting bothersome Miscrits to sleep with a mere gesture. They awaken hours later, confused and unaware of what transpired

name: Dark Monfiki
description: Dark Monfiki furiously chants dark incantations, its voice seething with rage. It never stops muttering, cursing everything around it, leaving those who listen dazed and uneasy

name: Foil Alionyx
description: Foil Alionyx refuses to budge, embedding its claws into the earth. Its radiant glow fortifies defenses while its venomous strikes linger dangerously

name: Foil Fangale
description: Foil Fangale's four keen eyes track every movement flawlessly. It glides with unparalleled grace, effortlessly weaving through the skies in perfect harmony with the wind

name: Dark Wiquill
description: The eerie blue flames on Dark Wiquill's back and face are widely believed to be the hottest in all of Miscrian Forest, burning without ever fading

name: Dark Krakenhook
description: Dark Krakenhook commands the sea Miscrits it has defeated, forcing them into its eerie crew. Those who resist face its venomous, crushing tentacles

name: Dark Mallardon
description: Dark Mallardon's chilling grip saps warmth from the water. It plays with struggling prey, only letting go once their strength is completely drained

name: Dark Willoak
description: Dark Willoak is a vengeful remnant of the Elder Tree, spreading decay wherever it roams, ensuring the forest never forgets its deepest grudges

name: Dark Rivett
description: Dark Rivett never speaks, only hums as it moves. Those who listen too closely claim to hear whispers buried beneath the sound

name: Dark Wyndasia
description: Many stories say the dark red gem on Dark Wyandasia's head glows when it finds something worth taking, but no one knows what it's searching for

name: Light Stomprage
description: Light Stomprage has an uncanny sense of direction, never getting lost even in total darkness. Some adventurers believe it can hear the whispers of the wind

name: Light Primordius
description: Light Primordius's shield is formed from the fossilized remains of the first Miscrit it defeated, preserved through ages by the flow of earth and water

name: Light Tornadouse
description: Light Tornadouse commands uncanny, slime-laced winds that blur vision and throw off its enemies' precision, making it incredibly difficult to catch

name: Light Praze
description: Light Praze's claws leave glowing blue scorch marks, easily tracking its movements. Its radiant flames light the way, marking its path as it moves with fiery precision

name: Light Afterburn
description: Light Afterburn's large size and heat resistance make it ideal for rescuing others from fires, using its fire and wind powers to control flames and protect those in danger

name: Light Thornaxis
description: Light Thornaxis strikes swiftly, using wind and nature to unleash poisonous attacks that weaken enemies while staying fast and elusive in battle

name: Plasmaree
description: Miscrian scientists have studied Plasmaree for decades, yet the secret behind its powerful plasma shields remains a mystery

name: Light Glitterglint
description: Light Glitterglint radiates joy, its glowing sparkles shifting with its mood. When threatened, it releases a brilliant flash that blinds and disorients enemies

name: Light Nessilisk
description: Light Nessilisk's piercing gaze intimidates foes. Its shimmering tail creates dazzling wind currents, and with a single burst of light, it leaves intruders utterly lost

name: Light Tuzee
description: Light Tuzee unleashes devastating attacks at a cost, often dazing itself. To compensate, it bolsters its defenses, ensuring resilience in the heat of battle

name: Light Kvetch
description: Light Kvetch enforces kindness with unwavering strength. Its calming energy maintains peace, ensuring harmony prevails wherever it roams

name: Light Incineron
description: Light Incineron wields its flames with masterful precision, melting barriers effortlessly. Its burning tongue leaves radiant trails, shaping the battlefield with calculated, scorching strikes

name: Light Krakenhook
description: Light Krakenhook, can be spotted playfully commanding water-type Miscrits at sea, using its glowing form to prank sailors and create harmless chaos on the waves

name: Light Excavior
description: Light Excavior, a legendary treasure hunter, uses its unparalleled senses and relentless determination to unearth hidden riches, breaking through solid ground to reveal long-buried secrets

name: Light Preliator
description: Known as the "Slayer of the Dark," it emerges when all seems lost, driving away shadows with its radiant might. Yet, little is known about its whereabouts, as it vanishes just as mysteriously as it appears

name: Light Sphynxus
description: Light Sphynxus enjoys crafting intricate riddles for other Miscrits, favoring mind games over combatthough it remains a formidable fighter when challenged

name: Dark Bifurcrystal
description: Dark Bifurcrystal is often called a living weaponrazor tails slash, a whip-like tongue cripples, and jagged teeth tear through even the toughest armor

name: Dark Obsidiape
description: The radiating heat from Dark Obsidiape's hands rivals an erupting volcano's magma, searing anything nearby with its dangerously intense power

name: Dark Abomino
description: Even under the blazing Miscrian sun, Dark Abomino remains encased in ice. However, its frozen coat no longer offers relief for those aroundinstead, it saps warmth, leaving only chilling exhaustion

name: Dark Ongabonga
description: Be careful of Dark Ongabonga's lightits glow may lead you astray. Adventurers are advised to learn how to distinguish it from its benevolent counterpart

name: Dark Gazaereal
description: Though Dark Gazaereal can fly with ease, it prefers to travel in sudden, powerful leaps. Those who see it mid-jump often mistake it for vanishing

name: Dark Incineron
description: Dark Incineron's Towering white flames twist unnaturally along its long limbs. Its cold fire burns through reality itself, leaving behind shimmering voids where the world once existed

name: Fortifield
description: Fortifield inspires camaraderie and competition, drawing tiny creatures to play on its back. Symbolizes unity, bringing creatures together through their shared love of the game

name: Dark Antennious
description: Dark Antennious moves silently in the shadows, its orbs dimmed to near-invisibility. When it strikes, they flash with a sinister glow, disorienting its prey in eerie darkness

name: Foil Antennious
description: Foil Antennious roams the night not as a hunter but a guide, lighting its orbs gently to lead lost travelers to safety before vanishing into the darkness

name: Cithreus
description: Citherus's fiery mane flows like molten gold, heating the air. Legends say it can summon solar flares with a roar, but only when provoked

name: Traumauler
description: Traumauler traps victims in eternal nightmares, feeding on fear. It targets those who disrupt nature's balance, serving as a guardian of both physical and spiritual realms

name: Light Serpasoar
description: Serpasoar's head and tail fight in perfect syncthe head battles head-on while the tail lands surprise strikes, seamlessly covering each other in combat

name: Dark Subterhuge
description: Dark Subterhuge has perfected its own brutal fighting style, using its immense strength and countless limbs to overwhelm opponents with relentless precision

name: Dark Weylani
description: Dark Weylani likes to drifts without purpose, indifferent to all around it. Those who follow in its wake often disappear, swallowed by the murky abyss

name: Blighted Fairyblossom
description: A nightmarish echo of its past, Blighted Fairyblossom's body is now a mass of corrupted petals and dark energy. It moves with terrifying speed, spreading decay wherever it goes

name: Dark Medustung
description: Dark Medustung's four lightning orbs never truly mergeinstead, they orbit endlessly, crackling with unstable energy, building a charge that threatens to unleash at any moment

name: Light Hawkogan
description: Hawkogan carries two radiant swords, it seeks a worthy opponent to prove their strength, ready to grant them one blade

name: Dark Alionyx
description: When Dark Alionyx refuses to move, it drives its gem claws deep, forming an impenetrable barrier. Yet when provoked, it charges with unstoppable force, its glowing crystals radiating defiance

name: Michelangelus
description: Michelangelus inspires mortals during crises, offering glimpses of its masterpieces. It meditates in ruins or whispers ideas to creators in dreams, remaining enigmatic in its methods

name: Light Leviafin
description: Despite Light Leviafin's shiny blue skin looking soft and fluffy, it is actually incredibly tough, capable of withstanding heavy blunt strikes with ease

name: Foil Geotoad
description: Foil Geotoad is a Miscrit from myth, the blinding brilliance of its sparkling crystal teeth is a sight only a few were granted. Many adventurers hunt it just to see it once

name: Blizzword
description: Broken horns don't stop Blizzword from using them in battle, instead utilising them as sharp blades. Having lived its life in harsh conditions, it's constantly venturing for new challenges

name: Dark Charrill
description: With its fire and frost locked in a never-ending battle, Dark Charrill, marked with icy sapphire embers, stands like a spectral sentinel

name: Coalrus
description: Coalrus's body naturally turns darker as he ages, and it's coal-like exterior doesn't mean he's naughty- really, he's quite nice

name: Starshow
description: Starshow has mastered the arts of surprise and destruction. It often screams SERKWORKS of UTUBIA! No one knows why it says this or what it means

name: Olmisteus
description: Olmisteus lurks in the darkest corners of the cave. Due to its blindness, it uses the mist it secretes as its main sense of sight to defend itself from predators

name: Caverachna
description: With its shell fully adapted to the Cave, Caverachna burrows itself underground to blend in. It spends most of its time sleeping and only attacks when it senses a threat

name: Thunderuff
description: Thunderuff has spent its life honing its stealth and agility. Once it sets its sights on something, there's no escaping it

name: Wicking
description: Wicking's tail is a formidable weapon, but it's best not to let it touch the ground - its roots can have a dangerous effect on the environment

name: Styrammuth
description: A giant that was once called "The Ruler of the Ice Age". It is said that Styrammuth can live for more than a thousand years due to its ability to change its environment with its control over the temperature

name: Citashell
description: Inside the icy structures of its shell Citashell hides and protects the weak little Miscrits lost in the snowstorm. It is strong enough to withstand the fiercest storm

name: Leffa
description: Leffa is usually assumed to be a brawny fool because of its huge body and tiny head, but it's actually a great thinker

name: Destructo
description: Destructo never emerges from its shell, and some believe it has become fused to it after years of residence

name: Tyrant
description: Tyrant's body is filled with actual magma, the heat of which turned its body grey and scaly

name: Moltrusian
description: Moltrusian crafted all of its armor on its own, and the craftsmanship is incredible. It has never made armor for humans despite many requests

name: Inhalate
description: Inhalate's glowing eyes appear just before you're surrounded by thick, sweet vapor. Some call it guardian: others, a warning

name: Carnagion
description: The leaves on Carnagion's feet look rather ordinary, but they are sharp enough to easily slice through nearly any substance

name: Sire
description: Sire is widely regarded as one of the wisest Miscrits of all. Despite his stately nature, though, he definitely knows how to have a good time

name: Chimpferno
description: Chimpferno's foes often look to its flaming appendages anticipating a hot battle. But surprisingly, its fists and talons are so powerful, it often chooses not to even scorch its foes

name: Lycanimbus
description: Lycanimbus' stormy wool allows it to produce powerful lightning that could strike down its prey in one attack. However, the thick hair makes its body slow and bulky

name: Gate Keeper
description: It's impossible to tell which hand belongs to which arm when Gate Keeper is using portals to fling its fists with reckless abandon

name: Lundevour
description: Large waves and earthquakes can indicate the presence of Lundevour in the water, under the ground, or in the sky. It can manipulate the sea, greatly increasing the flow and waves

name: Clawsteroid
description: Clawsteroid can easily punch massive meteors to dust in a split second. Scholars believe, if it weren't held back by the low gravity of the moon, a single attack could have catastrophic results

name: Noxilunar
description: Noxilunar can infect up to 50 creatures with its potent viral matter. It detects low-frequency sounds across the moon's galaxy through sonic waves absorbed by its body

name: Funglor
description: Funglor can reach incredible speeds underwater, allowing it to attack quickly or simply avoid battle if it's not in the mood and wants to be alone

name: Gemarax
description: Gemarax is fully encased in gem armor and revered as a guardian of lunar crystals. Its body stores cosmic energy, allowing it to lead colonies with overwhelming power

name: Void Warden
description: Thanks to its endless growth, Void Warden can get large enough to devour huge celestial bodies. This titan was given the moniker "Singularitas" by ancient civilization

name: Monodra
description: Born in the depths of the lunar caves, Monodra possesses incredible hearing, vision, and reaction time, as well as a rebellious nature that not everyone can tame

name: Bonefish
description: It is said that Bonefish's entire body is made up of the remains of an ancient monster from the deepest depths of the ocean. An equally ancient and powerful energy flows through its own bones

name: Progenitus
description: A celestial Miscrit that serves as the protector of the Moon, Progenitus has an ancient rivalry with Void Warden - one so great that their overwhelming power shook the moon itself

name: Egghead
description: Egghead tries to exercise its body as much as its mind, which is why it always wears weights on its tentacles

name: Novasol
description: Novasol cannot contain the energy it absorbs, causing its core to eventually collapse in an uncontrollable explosion. It's known as 'the star that never exploded'

name: Slimonda
description: Slimonda does not control its lightning tails during hibernation, which means that any creature nearby can be struck by a powerful electric shock

name: Mograkoon
description: Once every month, the Mograkoons gather in one area of the moon, where they engage in battles to test the strength of their armor and choose the leader with the most durable protection

name: Tyvalune
description: Tyvalune is the only Miscrit who cleans the moon's orbit of toxic deposits and debris, accumulating vital energy and saving the moon's inhabitants

name: Tenebu
description: Tenebu's levitation allows it to easily dodge attacks in combat, exhausting its opponent before delivering a devastating blow. It's an incredible spectacle

name: Vulcrysa
description: Despite the fact that the flame around Vulcrysa constantly rotates, they can masterfully control it with their tails so that nothing nearby gets burned

name: Vornaclast
description: A lunar drifter, wandering through the dark corners of the moon. Vornaclast often tears off its own tentacle before it mineralizes, using it as bait to hunt other creatures

name: Acarion
description: Acarion is cunning enough to give it an advantage in battle. The orbs on its tail shine treacherously brightly, distracting its opponents and allowing it to launch another attack

name: Magros
description: The ultimate amalgamation borne from the Miscrian Moon. Magros is better left alone, its resilient body will fend off most attacks. You should focus on surviving the encounter with it instead

name: Eclipsagon
description: Eclipsagon thrives in close combat. Flames on the back of Eclipsagon sear enemies which approach from behind. Upfront approach may be required if you dare to cross its path

name: Zevurnox
description: Zevurnox's body radiates lunar thunder. If its presence won't leave you illuminated, maybe the overflowing lightning from within their body will

name: Tenebros
description: Tenebros is a disciplined and shady fighter. They say any Miscrit who has turned their back on a Tenebros has lost in battle

name: Mystacle
description: Rather than obsessively protecting its water supplies, Mystacle chooses to turn primarily into steam so it can move more freely

name: Crateron
description: Crateron can create massive craters using pure energy expelled from its hand. The physics of it are quite impressive

name: Armageddon
description: Armageddon is named for the raw destruction it wreaks wherever it goes. With some of the most powerful attacks in Miscria, we're all very lucky it stays mostly on the moon

name: Infernofang
description: Infernofang, a feared lunar beast cloaked in corrupting green plasma, moves fast, leaves glowing trails, and sears with suffocating heat from its fangs

name: Valydorm
description: Valydorm's claws are powerful enough to shatter rocks on the moon in a few strikes, which is how it sharpens them before a real battle

name: Venoplazm
description: Venoplazm's cells react to dense spores, fusing it with nearby vegetation. It becomes highly aggressive, spreading fungal spores through its cytoplasm

name: Yutuluna
description: Yutuluna uses the patterns on its bioluminescent wings as a form of self defense from predators. These patterns resemble giant glowing eyes, which intimidates its opponents

name: Cnidalien
description: Cnidalien gather into herds and migrate all over the Moon in search of breeding grounds. It leaves a trail of poisonous residue behind

name: Mortovela
description: Mortovela is the cause of nightmares for most Miscrians, due to its eerie appearance. Equally eerie is the cold wind that will arrive from nowhere before Mortovela appears

name: Necroslime
description: The deadly acid that makes up the Necroslime can be transferred to the remains of other Miscrits, creating new Goos and starting the evolution cycle anew

name: Thanaross
description: Thanaross's flames are different from those of other Fire Miscrits, its burns may take longer to heal, causing victims to feel fear and panic upon Thanaross's subsequent gaze

name: Rupturea
description: Rupturea clicks its beak as it's about to deliver a wicked wind blast. Those hit by its magic never forget those dreadful sounds

name: Ectyros
description: No one has ever been able to see Ectyros' true face, and if anyone tries to look beneath its cloak, it immediately becomes a sham

name: Zatavol
description: Zatavol doesn't tolerate boredom and always finds a way to play, usually getting into trouble, even when its owner is around, who often ends up in trouble as well

name: Pirate Convincer
description: Pirate Convincer could use its tail for all kinds of useful tasks, but it's usually too busy sleeping off whatever it did the night before to bother

name: Sigarope
description: Sigarope's anatomy is similar to Frankensnarl's in many ways, but their energy is very different, and it is unclear whether Sigarope's crystals are the secret to its power

name: Kopul
description: The Demon of the Earth - this is how Kopul was nicknamed because of its intimidating appearance and incredible strength, causing its enemies to suffer not only physically but also mentally

name: Thundra
description: Thundra's readiness for battle can be determined by the brightness of the lightning surrounding it, and when it starts shining brighter than usual, it's best to stay away

name: Unbound
description: Free of its captivity, Unbound seeks hapless victims to trap in the Miscripedia that once held it prisoner, absorbing their essence to fuel its own magic

name: Scarecrow Carnagion
description: Scarecrow Carnagion's lantern is said to be fueled by the terror it strikes into the hearts of the wicked... but that's probably just a story

name: Vamp Sulfurious
description: Vamp Sulfurious sometimes tries to cover up its foul odor using flowers and perfumes, but it only makes things worse

name: Grimm Edison Ray
description: Grimm Edison Ray's scythe is so large that it cannot depend on the element of surprise, because it can be seen quite far away

name: Rocker Dischord
description: Rocker Dischord gets very upset at any suggestion that its music is really just noise and will fight back at anyone who says so

name: Boo Minotorch
description: No one is sure how Boo Minotorch manages not to set its sheet on fire, but somehow it remains un-torched

name: Netherreap
description: Netherreap walks the threshold of life and death, guiding souls to the afterlife with a quiet, final mercy

name: Zephtsune
description: Zephtsune has incredible strength and always fights mercilessly to the end. It is said that before it attacks, there is a whistling wind that chills the bones

name: Dark Buzzcargo
description: Dark Buzzcargo's brightly colored body serves as a warning of its poisonous nature. That's the only warning anyone gets

name: Stravatach
description: Stravatach feeds on the souls of deceased Fire Miscrits, coming to them when their time is up. No one knows if they do it willingly or if it is their true mission

name: Blackfin
description: Blackfin lives at such depths that it is almost never seen. The only light glimpsing it comes from the explosive energy balls it conjures by vibrating its fins at insane speed

name: Breocharn
description: Once its body has burnt to the ground, Breocharn will retire to hide and let its flame fade, after which it will build a new body from scratch, becoming a Poppet once more

name: Mrakovlad
description: Mrakovlad is one of the wisest Miscrits, teaching other Miscrits of the Lightning element. For some reason, it has a strong dislike for all Miscrits of the Wind element

name: Makras
description: The gold jewelry on Makras's body is incredibly valuable, but not just because it shines brightly. The patterns on it are unique to each Makras, reflecting their character

name: Cthulith
description: With her devilishly beautiful appearance, Cthulith lures her prey into a mindless trance before incinerating them with her eldritch flame. Many Miscrians argue that Cthulith's beauty even rivals that of Mermafox

name: Beruette
description: Beruette is empty inside - both emotionally and physically. It feels nothing but the need to absorb electricity, channeling it through its monstrous maul

name: Bakuyaga
description: Legends tell that Bakuyaga's weaving skills were taught to them by a ghostly seamstress, knowledge they later passed down to their own kin

name: Toucanaconda
description: Toucanaconda's wings are purely decorative, and it cannot actually get off the ground. It instead uses them to make itself bigger, in order to intimidate its foes

name: Octopuff
description: Octopuff will win almost any one-on-one fight it gets into with other wild Miscrits, and often just puffs up to intimidate its foes into running away so it doesn't have to go to the trouble of a battle

name: Gryndle
description: Gryndle is often too dignified to engage in random fights, but when it does decide to battle, it is relentlessly powerful

name: Dark Serpasoar
description: Dark Serpasoar wants to win at any cost, and has no honor or integrity when it comes to battling

name: Spikrus
description: Spikrus tail and tongue are tinged purple with a deadly poison which it rarely chooses to employ

name: Foil Pixiuma
description: Enemies think twice before challenging Foil Pixiuma. It is so intimidating that most challengers give up before the fight has a chance to begin

name: Sharkranha
description: Despite its fearsome appearance, Sharkranha is a gentle giant who usually holds back while battling in order to avoid hurting anyone

name: Stumperback
description: Stumperback spends its life hunting for whomever chopped the tree from its back, and battles mainly so it can be stronger for that eventual fight

name: Sporott
description: Sporott is extremely spry and quick to attack any approaching foes. He has the most dangerous poison of any Miscrit currently known

name: Vaporo
description: Every movement of Vaporo is as graceful as it is dangerous, as it loves to trick its opponents before unleashing a massive wave

name: Dark Vesuvion
description: Dark Vesuvion's rage is completely uncontrollable. It explodes without any warning, injuring any who are foolish enough to go near it

name: Vampvine
description: Vampvine feeds on other Miscrits while they sleep. It takes enough health from them to repower itself without awakening them

name: Mirindo
description: Mirindo's poison is considered one of the most dangerous in Miscria, as it affects the victim's nervous system and causes severe pain, regardless of whether it is Miscrit or human

name: Kyubigama
description: Kyubigama is a nine-tailed Miscrit spoken of in ancient tales. Said to be a guardian of life, it's believed to bring great fortune to those who witness its power

name: Helioxic
description: Helioxic's flameball is filled with a burning hot, poisonous material that it only deploys in the most dire of situations

name: Dungaroll
description: Dungaroll moves around very awkwardly because of its short little legs and gigantic belly, which makes it very self-conscious

name: Invatorres
description: Invatorres has gathered minerals from all over Miscria to make its incredible exoskeleton. It has an eerie glow which helps to frighten off those who find its hiding place

name: Blowstoll
description: Blowstoll's slowness and clumsiness are compensated by its super strong shell and ability to create monstrous waves

name: Foil Invatorres
description: Foil Invatorres is said to sparkle more than any other Foil Miscrit because of the reaction between the minerals in its exoskeleton and the Foil

name: Behemammoth
description: Behemammoth's age can be measured by how tightly its tusks are curled. As it ages, the curls grow smaller and tighter

name: Blargles
description: The gems on Blargles' forehead are the source of most of its power, and it will protect them from attackers by any means necessary

name: Perenniax
description: The colors of Perenniax's petals glow with a much deeper, richer color right after it wins an important battle

name: Pitheyaur
description: Farmers love Pitheyaur because it's not aggressive and helps crops grow faster, but its body is covered in thorns, so it's best not to touch it

name: Dark Popiller
description: Dark Popiller could have been one of the kindest and most charming Miscrits in the land, but loneliness and the indifference of others turned it into a monster

name: Baloognio
description: Baloognio believes it's the king of the Jungle, empowering itself by draining energy from those it considers lesser. Its crown grows in size the more power it amasses.

name: Foil Growliath
description: Foil Growliath is more dependable than the normal version, and it can always be counted on to make a great difference in battle

name: Mermafox
description: Mermafox is a beautiful white fox, the guardian and mermaid of the sea. One whip from its powerful tail could resist the fiercest storm
